  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "In a blender or food processor, combine coconut oil, onion, garlic, and lemongrass stalks. Blend until smooth.",
    "In a medium skillet, cook cauliflower over medium heat until tender, about 5 minutes.",
    "In a separate bowl, whisk together Greek yogurt, mozzarella cheese, cheddar cheese, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Grease six 6-ounce ramekins with coconut oil and sprinkle with shredded mozzarella cheese.",
    "Divide cooked cauliflower among the ramekins, followed by the yogurt-cheese mixture, and top with lemongrass onion mixture.",
    "Pour coconut cream over the cheese mixture, then sprinkle with additional mozzarella cheese and parsley.",
    "Bake for 20-25 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly.",
    "Serve immediately and enjoy!",
    "Let ramekins cool for 5 minutes before serving."
  ],
